    <p> I then continued by bus to the hostel, the Haka Lodge. This is really nice and highly recommended. Nice small company with a sleeping hall with 7 single beds. These are divided into 2/3 groups and with thin walls from each other under the roof. Which conveys a little the feeling of privacy. The common room was also quite well equipped, maintained and modern. A place where you can go well. The people who live there were very nice and helpful. To have the staff very friendly and always for fun. I can only say that I haven't laughed as much for a long time and as hearty as in the 3 days there. </p>
    <p> I then spent my birthday with 2 of the boys staying there longer in the botanical garden in search of beautiful motifs for our cameras. </p>
