    <p> Actually, I wanted to go to a range zoo but only I didn't get an answer to my email in which I asked about the shuttle service offered and when I called I told me that the Setvice should cost $ 60 back and forth. That was a bit too expensive for me because another $ 28 would get there. So the excursion would cost almost &euro; 60. That is really too much money for me to go to a zoo. </p>
    <p> In the afternoon I baked my birthday cake myself and nibbled together with everyone present. Was a really good tarte de Santiago. It was a very pleasant day. Everything is quite relaxed, apart from the egg with a manual hand mixer. </p>
    <p> The next day we went to Australia. But before I flew there, I should experience a little earthquake. When I just grabbed my things, suddenly the padlocks on the personal subjects of the guests started to clatter. It took about 30 seconds and before I realized what was going on, it was over again. It later turned out that it was an earthquake of the strength 4. The epicenter was the newly created fault line west of Christchurch. </p>
